> <OLD>
>
> At this point, as he saw something far off in the distance, beyond the
> ability of his optics to make out clearly, WHEELIE shifted over to his robot
> mode, ducking low agaisnt the bad terrain, and went to pull out a set of
> macrobinoculars.  Going to try and use them to lock on from afar if he could
> to see what it was, if anything could be made out.

<NEW>

It was difficult to make anything out with all the intervening
underbrush. However after a moment he could make out what appeared to
be a tree had fallen judging by the damage to some of the brush around
it.

As WHEELIE maneuvered closer he could see it was spanning a small but
very deep gorge, the sound of water could vaguely be heard rushing
through it somewhere below. Around and over the gorge there were the
shapes of large avian creatures flying around the fallen tree.

SWOOP, TERRANOTRON and LAZORBEAK.

(OOC: Basically all redecos of each other and Terrorsaur and all of
the DINOBOTS!)

- Preston
